   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Motash:  I usaully start off pulling the urhail so i have at least one creature in hand and then top 4 the rest.  From that i will play at least 2 creatures depending on what i draw and if i go second and get the ormagon+creature+impact only if it is nessary.  But i use Motash as a drawer since she is the best drawer for underneath given the right creatures.  Over all i try not to be much on the offence enless i pull a strags claws and have enough energy to attack and keep the creatures alive.<br>
<br>
Radget:  Usually i keep out at least one parmalag and keep it powered up with refresh.  but other than that is just keeping the oppenet under control with teh spells and creatures<br>
<br>
Fossik:  All i can say is do what its takes to finish them off.  The Crytal Jile is nice ian get 2 uses out of it.<br>
<br>
Relics:  The relics used is just basic support for the deck to help it out.  The jewel are really nice to discards the Urhail to draw or the ormagons/Gorgles curses if faceing underneath.  Strags claws are usually use on Motash or radget to keep the creatures going.<br>
<br>
Spells:  Besides the Impact the all teh spells can help in creature control some how.  Resonates Rule!!! The crushing fungus are great they can hold off an oppenent for a turn at times which underneath needs to makes a good move.<br>
<br>
Creatures:  Sikra!!! ahhh they just rule :) and the Akkars do to with Motash.  Crystal Parmalag are really nice with Radget and even Fossik.  And everything else is basically standard Gons, urhail, and other starting cards.  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
